<UserControl x:Class="Fhi.Controls.Indicators.Governance.Wizard.Step1"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:local="clr-namespace:Fhi.Controls.Indicators.Governance.Wizard"
             xmlns:utils="clr-namespace:Fhi.Controls.Utils"
             mc:Ignorable="d"
             d:DataContext="{d:DesignInstance local:Step1ViewModel}"
             d:DesignHeight="300"
             d:DesignWidth="300">
    <Grid>
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
            <RowDefinition/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        <TextBlock Text="Setup for Governance Indicators"
                   Grid.Row="0"
                   FontSize="16"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   Margin="10"
                   HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
        <TextBlock Grid.Row="1"
                   Margin="20"
                   TextWrapping="Wrap">
            <Run>
                This wizard will guide you through importing basin stakeholder survey data
                which forms the basis for the governance indicators.
            </Run>
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run>
                The first step is to open the survey in Excel and note the column which holds the
                user identifier and the column in which the questions begin. The default for the user
                identification is column 'A', and the default for the questions is column 'K'.
            </Run>
            <LineBreak/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run>
                Next, notice that the last question in a given group starts with the same thing and
                that's how we determine question grouping. If necessary, you can modify what the last
                question starts with. The default is 'Please provide'.
            </Run>
        </TextBlock>
        <Grid Grid.Row="2">
            <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
                <ColumnDefinition/>
                <ColumnDefinition/>
            </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <StackPanel Grid.Column="0">
                <TextBlock Text="User Identifier Column"
                           Margin="5"
                           HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
                <ComboBox SelectedItem="{Binding UserColumn}"
                          ItemsSource="{Binding ColumnChoices}"
                          Margin="5"
                          Width="50"
                          HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
            </StackPanel>
            <StackPanel Grid.Column="1">
                <TextBlock Text="Questions Starting Column"
                           Margin="5"
                           HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
                <ComboBox SelectedItem="{Binding QuestionColumn}"
                          ItemsSource="{Binding ColumnChoices}"
                          Margin="5"
                          Width="50"
                          HorizontalAlignment="Center"/>
            </StackPanel>
            
        </Grid>
        <StackPanel Grid.Row="3"
                    HorizontalAlignment="Center">
            <TextBlock Text="Last question in group starts with:"
                       Margin="5"/>
            <TextBox Text="{Binding LastQuestion}"
                     Width="200"
                     Margin="5"/>
        </StackPanel>
        <utils:ContextHelp Grid.Row="3"
                           Url="Governance_and_Stakeholders/Survey.html"
                           HorizontalAlignment="Right"
                           VerticalAlignment="Bottom"/>
    </Grid>
</UserControl>
